# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# .env.example — copy this file to `.env` for local development and fill in
# your own BCCR bearer token. The real `.env` is gitignored so credentials
# never land in version control.
#
# How to obtain a bearer token from BCCR:
# 1. Register a user account at the BCCR developer portal
#    (https://www.bccr.fi.cr/indicadores-economicos/servicio-web).
# 2. Inside the portal, issue a bearer token for the
#    "Publico.Indicadores.API" product.
# 3. Copy the token string and paste it below.
#
# The server reads only BCCR_TOKEN — it never asks for your username or
# password. The token is attached to every outbound BCCR request as
# `Authorization: Bearer <token>`.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------

BCCR_TOKEN=replace-me-with-your-bearer-token
